OL,3,CWoman who underwent mesh surgery says
OL,4,Csurgeon should be banned
OL,6,FToday (18 July), Mr Dixon was
OL,7,Fsuspended from practicing medicine for
OL,8,Fsix months after a tribunal ruled he
OL,9,Ffailed to provide adequate clinical
OL,10,Fcare.
OL,12,FMr Dixon maintains he always acted in
OL,13,Fgood faith and that complications can
OL,14,Farise from surgery. He has issued an
OL,15,Fapology to his patients.
OL,17,FBut Ms Buse claims the side effects
OL,18,Fshe experienced were so severe she has
OL,19,Fnow been registered disabled, and is
OL,20,Fprescribed morphine to live with the
OL,21,Fpain.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/12
